  "body": "*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n\r\n*Summary*: I have scanned QR code of someone. I went to this chat and wanted to send a transaction. While being on transaction screen i tapped sign later. I deleted the chat with this person. Then i went to Unsigned and signed the transaction. I do expect the chat which i deleted earlier is shown again.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\ni want the chat to be re-opened after deletion when i trigger it by sending transaction from sign later screen. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nchat is not shown on the sender side\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Faucet some funds\r\n- Scan valid QR code of any person\r\n- call /send command and tap sign later on transaction screen\r\n- on the home tab delete the chat with this person\r\n- tap wallet - transaction history - unsigned\r\n- sign the transaction\r\n- pay attention that no chat was re-created\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
